{"id": "1409498876800532531", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "120677325137379328", "author_name": "crimsondream24", "content": "Her story wasn't very well written. I forget her name but Horla grew up with her best friend and they were incredibly close but for some reason being jealous that Horla's poems were being praised was somehow enough for her to kill Horla. Very bad writting.", "timestamp": "2025-08-25T11:25:19.452000+00:00"}
{"id": "1409543432589807709", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "503572143590866955", "author_name": "nazhigezihk", "content": "I think not exactly jealousy, they were best friends and the gardener bears all the life burdens for her. Until she started receiving money from the press, that was an amount she has to work her ass off by being a gardener. She took the fame and most of the money, saying the poems are not popular enough and Horla should always write more. After a while she was infected with dissolution and her guilt turned  into obsession and paranoids. She monitored Horla 24 hours non stop and belives everyone, the readers and Horla, was mocking at her. Yet Horla trusted her till her last moment", "timestamp": "2025-08-25T14:22:22.380000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["120677325137379328"], "reply_to": "1409498876800532531"}
