{"id": "1409562653445329067", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "173543218573606913", "author_name": "madoor", "content": "Throughout their past colette (horla's ~~girl~~friend) is portrayed as someone who is particularly ambitious and focused on wealth/power, as she wants to one day own not only the garden her and horla are renting out, but also the mansion of the landlord of that garden. (It's also shown in how she doesn't understand the meaning behind horla's poems and thinks that they don't hold much value) Combined with that, colette also said she would \"bear the thorns\" for horla while they were living together, which is shown as her taking care of most of the work and money related troubles for the two. (which was likely long and exhausting for barely enough money to keep them afloat) While colette's love for horla was enough to keep her (mostly) content with the situation, when horla's poems were finally published and earned her a significant amount of money and fame, its implied that's what pushed colette over the edge and ended up with her starting the fire.", "timestamp": "2025-08-25T15:38:44.989000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["120677325137379328"], "reply_to": "1409498876800532531"}
{"id": "1409563357534748784", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "173543218573606913", "author_name": "madoor", "content": "And while even that may seem like a shaky reasoning for what colette did, it's also (kind of) shown that it was a mostly impulsive decision that she immediately came to regret, which she then sort of ended up deluding herself into thinking that it was justified to escape from her guilt.", "timestamp": "2025-08-25T15:41:32.857000+00:00"}
{"id": "1409563529262141480", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "173543218573606913", "author_name": "madoor", "content": "since colette wasn't shown to be infected by dissolution until much later after horla's death, i dont really think that has much to do with her actions in the past, though it is a big factor in her actions during the present events of the special ops", "timestamp": "2025-08-25T15:42:13.800000+00:00"}
